This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with network traffic anomaly detection, which is a common problem in cybersecurity. The use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper's focus on identifying previously unseen patterns in network traffic suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
